title: Women's World Cup will embolden players to fight for the pay they deserve
description: Everything you will see at the Women's World Cup the players had to fight for.

title: Ousted leader's son calls on governments to impose 'tougher sanctions' on Myanmar
description: International governments should impose "tougher sanctions" on Myanmar and restrict its military from accessing aviation fuel, the son of the country's ousted leader has said.

title: Putin is balanced on a delicate tightrope when it comes to Prigozhin
description: A little less than two weeks ago, we were taken to the camp at Tsel where Yevgeny Prigozhin appears to have popped up.

title: US soldier's illegal border crossing into North Korea mistaken as TikTok stunt by tourist
description: A tourist who saw a US soldier run across the North Korean border said she first thought it was part of a TikTok stunt.

title: Thousands of acres of blackened wasteland show the climate crisis is very real - and it's getting worse
description: The speed these fires are spreading is truly frightening.

title: Wagner mercenary boss Prigozhin 'seen welcoming his fighters to Belarus'
description: Russian mercenary boss Yevgeny Prigozhin has purportedly appeared in a video welcoming his fighters to Belarus and saying their training will make the Belarusian army the second best in the world.

title: Putin will not attend summit in South Africa amid arrest warrant
description: Vladimir Putin will not be attending the BRICS trade summit in South Africa thereby avoiding the risk of arrest.

title: Is Russia’s invasion of Ukraine ‘doomed’?
description: Senior Ukrainian military officials believe Russia is planning a massive attack in the northeastern Kharkiv region in a bid to draw Ukraine's efforts away from its counteroffensive.

title: German businesses 'should consider allowing staff siestas' as temperatures hit 38C
description: Businesses in Germany should consider allowing staff to take midday siestas, according to a public health chief, as temperatures in the country soar.

title: Cost of living sparks riots as police use tear gas and water cannon on protestors
description: At least four people have been injured in clashes with riot police during demonstrations against the rising cost of living in Kenya.

title: China has 'a responsibility' for the 'tragic' situation in Myanmar
description: China has a responsibility for the "tragic" situation in Myanmar because it is the "foremost supporter" of the military regime, the head of the British foreign intelligence service MI6 has said.

title: The Americans who have gone to North Korea - including soldiers
description: A US soldier who is believed to have crossed into North Korea is not the first American to enter the secretive country. What has become clear over the years is that getting out can be much harder than getting in.

title: Tony Blair desperate to avoid reports of 'snuggling up' to Silvio Berlusconi, files show
description: Tony Blair was desperate to avoid being seen as "snuggling up" to Italian leader Silvio Berlusconi, official documents of the early-noughties have revealed.

title: Russians appalled by Ukraine war should spy for UK, says MI6 boss
description: The head of MI6 has urged Russians appalled by the horrors of Vladimir Putin's war in Ukraine to "join hands with us" and spy for the UK to help end the bloodshed.
